<paragraph id="D5CEC365F425999589A5C7DFF9C893AD" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="7E10DE625B2D77293DD916A721C74B38" LSID="5F272E50-3880-8ABC-6CED-DC5CFB0F4A7B" authority="Dejean, 1826" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1826" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Sphaeroderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphaeroderus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sphaeroderus Dejean, 1826</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8AFD446DDD0385E37874A3A438B9259F" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="766E6212F58E5205B3596F5CAA9A635C" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
<taxonomicName id="4203BA118ADE8DAF8D860A7D59CFE3AD" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1826" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Sphaeroderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sphaeroderus</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1826: 14. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="ACB4A9C79E572A3D9629CFEF787E0956" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1826" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Sphaeroderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lecontei">
<emphasis id="021DA081644FF60F94BCB621AEE4D488" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Sphaeroderus lecontei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1826 designated by Hope (1838: 65). Etymology (original). From the Greek 
<emphasis id="2D984C044CBEB11B85208E0D5A747D24" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">sphaera</emphasis>
(sphere) and 
<emphasis id="3EFD5E5C83D51BD7A6AC9CB70965DBED" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">dere</emphasis>
(neck, by extension pronotum), alluding to the round or oval shape of the pronota (&quot; 
<emphasis id="DF89DC72D2321D61FC48DE6D326CD703" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">corselet</emphasis>
... 
<emphasis id="734A13AE22B1607A206402CE80C8CDD2" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
arrondi, ovale ou 
<normalizedToken id="6CA4D56E8639121D0E0D18CE387955F2" originalValue="orbiculé">orbicule</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
&quot;) of the species then known to Dejean [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="194DC6F474B7BF20C77043A3CDB1816D" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="83C7E500D7013F90E08E5AB128A31EA7" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AD0424939780E41BE136AE4410D4E7B8" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Six species restricted to the boreal and temperate regions of eastern North America.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="178B3904A8FDEC781F68C59EEAAA2B92" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" type="identification">
<paragraph id="E42A5902D58BA06E3E3151AE7660067D" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ECDC809373111CE1989C79C4CF289C99" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
<normalizedToken id="615851EB7F3F6EA0F3D17B147373A77C" originalValue="Lindroth’s">Lindroth's</normalizedToken>
(1961a) key covers four of the species currently recognized; 
<taxonomicName id="C96A5D21E78A2FFCD5E6BD6F31BCDC0D" baseAuthorityName="Blatchley" baseAuthorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Sphaeroderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indianae">
<emphasis id="3FB92E8CF55AE5B34761A71A44881C56" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Sphaeroderus indianae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not included and 
<taxonomicName id="399783E0A6F2C37FB4FF3617ED078511" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1861" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Sphaeroderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schaumii">
<emphasis id="BAC71C428CD9F180FB578A14D142533A" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Sphaeroderus schaumii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="E7B8F299D807D38281D37075FE36B62A" authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Sphaeroderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidicollis">
<emphasis id="38ABAB59A668902FEF1EB37235B9AF67" italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Sphaeroderus nitidicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A taxonomic revision of the genus is needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
